The paper deals with clustering problems, which are often studied in the areas of data mining (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The specific problems studied, Starforest Editing and Bicluster Editing, are related to graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered in the categories of computational geometry (cs.CG) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The paper also mentions multivariate subexponential time algorithms, which are relevant to machine learning and statistics (cs.LG).
